**ğŸ³ Local Installation Steps**

**Option 1: Docker (Easiest - Recommended)**

\# STEP 1: Install Docker Desktop (if you don\'t have it)

\# Download from: https://www.docker.com/products/docker-desktop

\# STEP 2: Run Qdrant container

\# EXPLANATION: This downloads Qdrant image and runs it locally

\# -d = run in background (detached mode)

\# -p 6333:6333 = expose port 6333 (API)

\# -p 6334:6334 = expose port 6334 (gRPC - optional)

\# -v = mount local folder for data persistence

docker run -d -p 6333:6333 -p 6334:6334 \\

-v \$(pwd)/qdrant_storage:/qdrant/storage \\

\--name qdrant \\

qdrant/qdrant

\# STEP 3: Verify it\'s running

curl http://localhost:6333

\# Should return: {\"title\":\"qdrant - vector search engine\",\...}

\# Or visit in browser: http://localhost:6333/dashboard

**What this does:**

-   Downloads Qdrant (\~200MB, one-time download)

-   Runs on localhost:6333

-   Stores data in ./qdrant_storage folder on your computer

-   Persists data even when you restart container

**Managing the container:**

\# Stop Qdrant

docker stop qdrant

\# Start Qdrant again

docker start qdrant

\# View logs

docker logs qdrant

\# Remove container (if you want to start fresh)

docker rm -f qdrant

